CatDescriptText: Mr. Ed Turner, mail handler, Bryn Mawr Road, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1962, pg. 11 with question: "As a newspaper, readser, what type of stories have the greatest appeal to you; In other words, which stories do you read first?" Answer reads: "naturally the headlines and then I try to get as much of the current news as possible, then the local, state, and branch from there to the national . The type varies, but right now I'm concerned with the new redevelopment because it affects me."
